  abstract  = {as well as alterations in the thickness, area, and folding pattern of the cortex. While surface-based analyses that 1 Massachusetts General Hospital Nuclear Magnetic Resonance Center depend on models of the position and orientation of the cortical ribbon can provide an accurate assessment of Rm. 2328, Building 149 13th Street cortical variability, volumetric techniques are required to detect changes in noncortical structures. For example,},
  file      = {:Fischl2002a - Neurotechnique Whole Brain Segmentation_ Automated Labeling of Neuroanatomical Structures in the Human Brain Structural Changes in the Brain. These Changes Can Cause Alterations in the Imaging Properties of Brain Tissue, As Well As Chang.pdf:PDF},
