  abstract = {The impo ance of anda d fo ha ing of comp a ional model and da a R ell A Pold ack (S anfo d Uni e i), F anklin Feingold (S anfo d Uni e i), Michael J F ank (B o n Uni e i), Pad aig Glee on (Uni e i College London), Gille de Hollande (V ije Uni e i ei Am e dam), Q en in JM H (Uni e i College London), B adle C. Lo e (Uni e i College London), Ch i ophe J. Ma kie ic (S anfo d Uni e i), Ro al n Mo an (King College London), Pe a Ri e (Cha i Uni e i medi in Be lin & Be lin In i e of Heal h), B andon M. T ne (The Ohio S a e Uni e i), Tal Ya koni (Uni e i of Te a a A in), Ming Zhan (Na ional In i e of Men al Heal h, NIH), Jona han D. Cohen (P ince on Uni e i) Ab ac The Ta ge A icle b Lee e al. (2019) highligh he a in hich ongoing conce n abo e ea ch ep od cibili e end o model-ba ed app oache in cogni i e cience. Whe ea Lee e al. foc p ima il on he impo ance of e ea ch p ac ice o imp o e model ob ne , e p opo e ha he an pa en ha ing of model pecifica ion , incl ding hei inp and o p , i al o e en ial o imp o ing he ep od cibili of model-ba ed anal e. We o line an ongoing effo (i hin he con e of he B ain Imaging Da a S c e comm ni) o de elop anda d fo he ha ing of he c e of comp a ional model and hei o p .},
